 The suspects with the rams  The suspects were arrested at the popular Mayor bus stop when the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) Ogijo Division, CSP Suleman Baba Muhammed, was on routine patrol of the area with his men and accosted the duo in a bus with registration number LSD 381 XN loaded with two big rams. According to spokesman of Ogun State command, Abimbola Oyeyemi, “on interrogation, the two suspects were unable to give satisfactory account of how they come about the rams hence they were arrested and taken to the station. On further questioning, they confessed that the rams were actually stolen. “While the investigation was going on, the owner of the rams who had been contacted appeared in the station with clear evidence of ownership of the two rams”.Meanwhile, the commissioner of police, CP Bashir Makama, has ordered a full investigation into the activities of the suspects with a view to charge them to court as soon as investigation is concluded.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .